ion chassis, turn on the chassis.  Turn on any external hard drives and wait for them to spin up.  Turn on all control surfaces and modules.  Turn on any MIDI interfaces, devices, and synchronization peripherals.  Turn on Pro Tools hardware.  Start your computer.  Turn on your audio monitors or amplifiers.  When powering down, do so in the opposite order.  285      S E T T  I  N G     U P     A N D    I  N T E G R A T  I  N G     C O N T R O L    S U R F A C E S    Index  Note to the Reader: Throughout this index  boldfaced page numbers indicate primary discus- sions of a topic. Italicized page numbers indicate illustrations.  A a cappella, alternate mixes for, 207 A-to-D  analog-to-digital  conversion, 27 AAF  Advanced Authoring Format , 237 Absolute Grid mode, 106 absolute time, 108 Accel expansion cards, 262 acoustic guitars  microphones for, 15 mix processing for, 195–196, 195–196 recording, 22–23, 23  acoustics in mastering, 227 Add Remove Controller command, 79 Add Tempo Change button, 11 addition for edit selection, 98 ADR  Automated Dialog Replacement , 259 Advanced Audio Coding  MPEG-4 AAC , 215 Advanced Authoring Format  AAF , 237 Advanced tab for MIDI, 46 ADVC100 transcoder, 236 After Playback scrolling option, 93 AIFF files, 233 ALAC  Apple Lossless encoder  format, 215 Algorithm Reverb Type setting, 161 All Automation option, 203 All group, 182 All Sample-Based Markers and Tracks option  All Tick-Based Markers & Tracks option  for Cut Time, 130 for Insert Time, 129  for Cut Time, 130 for Insert Time, 129  alternate mix versions, 206–207 alternate playlist recording techniques, 37–40,  37–40  AM radio plug-in, 153–155, 153–154 Amp Farm plug-in, 153  amplifiers  for electric guitars, 19 for lead vocals, 26 for microphones, 21 in mixing, 186 overview, 27  AmpliTube plug-in, 153 analog flavor in mixing, 211 analog-to-digital  A-to-D  conversion, 27 Apple Lossless encoder  ALAC  format, 215 Apply SRC option, 119 arpeggiators, 84 asymmetric fades, 126, 126 At